<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup></font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup>McKinsey &amp; Company, &#8220;Delivering through Diversity&#8221;, January 2018<br />(https://www.mckinsey.com/~/media/mckinsey/business%20functions/organization/our%20insights/delivering%20through%20diversity/delivering-through-diversity_full-report.ashx)</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:-4.54%;font-size:3pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup>Holger, Dieter, &#8220;The business case for more diversity&#8221; Wall Street Journal, October 26, 2019 (https://www.wsj.com/articles/the-business-case-for-more-diversity-11572091200)</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:-4.54%;font-size:3pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;&#160;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup></font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup>McKinsey &amp; Company, &#8220;Women in the Workplace 2018&#8221;, (https://womenintheworkplace.com/)</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:4.54%;text-indent:-4.54%;font-size:3pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">&#160;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup></font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup>https://www.asyousow.org/our-work/gender-workplace-equity-disclosure-statement</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD66"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD66"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has determined that this proposal would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As the proponent acknowledges, Tesla published in December 2020 our first Diversity, Equity and Inclusion Impact Report, which outlined our diversity, equity and inclusion (&#8220;<font style="text-decoration:underline;">DEI</font>&#8221;) programs and future roadmap for further actions we are taking to engage with employees, candidates and community members on DEI issues. Data from this Report was then integrated into Tesla&#8217;s annual Impact Report published in August 2021 and Tesla will continue to publish an integrated Impact Report including DEI information going forward. Moreover, as only the third iteration of the Impact Report, it is our goal to continuously assess and improve the Report from year to year. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla and the Board are proud of the strides made so far. For example, as part of our inaugural set of DEI metrics, Tesla disclosed the percentages of our workforce and leadership who are women, come from underrepresented communities, or are veterans, and further provided employment percentages respectively for our employees representing Black/African American, Asian, Hispanic/LatinX and other underrepresented communities. In addition, Tesla disclosed the percentages of new hires and promotions who are women or come from underrepresented communities. At this time, we believe that these are the appropriate metrics to allow our stockholders to monitor the progress of our DEI efforts, and they convey even more than the broad categories of information specifically mentioned by the proponent&#8212;racial and ethnic diversity, gender diversity, the hiring of women, and women and people of color in management positions. The proponent has not indicated how the presentation of full EEO-1 data, which further breaks down employee information primarily by categories of job functions, would promote a more diverse workforce or provide investors with a better understanding of Tesla&#8217;s DEI policies and practices. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Moreover, the Impact Report also describes the ways in which the Board is involved in Tesla&#8217;s DEI reporting. For example, Board members regularly engage with our human resources leadership to review and align with Tesla&#8217;s DEI progress and provide feedback as to the effectiveness of its program.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">For these reasons, we believe that the current scope of Tesla&#8217;s reporting is appropriate to provide our stockholders with visibility into our DEI program and a way to track its progress over time. </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding additional reporting on diversity and inclusion efforts.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">21</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_SEVEN"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_SEVEN"></a>PROPOSAL SEVEN</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING REPORTING ON EMPLOYEE ARBITRATION</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with SEC rules, we have set forth below a stockholder proposal, along with a supporting statement, exactly as submitted from Nia Impact Capital. Nia Impact Capital has notified us that it is the beneficial owner of 923 shares of Tesla&#8217;s common stock and intends to present the following proposal at the 2021 Annual Meeting. Nia Impact Capital&#8217;s address is 1212 Preservation Parkway, Suite 200, Oakland, CA 94612. The stockholder proposal will be required to be voted upon at the 2021 Annual Meeting only if properly presented.&#160;&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME6"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME6"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:8pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Shareholders of Tesla, Inc. (&#8220;Tesla&#8221;) ask the Board of Directors to oversee the preparation of a public report on the impact of the use of mandatory arbitration on Tesla&#8217;s employees and workplace culture. The report should evaluate the impact of Tesla&#8217;s current use of arbitration on the prevalence of harassment and discrimination in its workplace and on employees&#8217; ability to seek redress. The report should be prepared at reasonable cost and omit proprietary and personal information.</p>
<p style="margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:8pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">WHEREAS:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A workplace that tolerates harassment and discrimination invites legal, brand, financial, and human capital risk. Companies may experience reduced morale, lost productivity, absenteeism, and challenges in attracting and retaining talent. A number of studies have found significant share value benefits associated with diverse, equitable and inclusive workplaces.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla requires employees to agree to arbitrate employment-related claims. In its 2020 proxy statement, Tesla stated that its arbitration proceedings are private if a &#8220;court rules that the underlying claims are subject to arbitration.&#8221; Tesla also stated that employees are allowed &#8220;remedies available in a court of law.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup> However, arbitrated employees may not access the courts directly, waive rights to all forms of judicial relief and may not bring class-action lawsuits.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Mandatory arbitration limits employees&#8217; remedies for wrongdoing, reduces employee willingness to report discrimination<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup>, and prevents their learning about shared concerns.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup> It may enable further discrimination, reduce workforce effectiveness, and create brand, legal and human capital risks. It masks from investors true workplace conditions.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">These concerns are particularly relevant to Tesla. Employees who sought court trials but whose cases were held in arbitration have alleged experiencing sexual harassment, discrimination, racism and violent threats. In California, over 140 discrimination complaints have been filed with the Department of Fair Employment and Housing .<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup> In New York, at least 12 employees anonymously brought concerns to a Buffalo news station.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Ongoing use of employee arbitration creates a long-tail risk for Tesla, particularly as arbitration clauses face a changing regulatory landscape. The Biden Administration stated within its campaign platform its intention to reduce arbitration&#8217;s use and some states, such as New York, have sought to retroactively release employees from arbitration agreements when discrimination concerns exist.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">A number of companies have ceased to require employees to arbitrate discrimination claims. This includes Google, whose use of arbitration was identified as a key aspect of a &#8220;culture of concealment&#8221; in its $310 million misconduct settlement.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Companies with effective human capital management programs, as Tesla claims to have, should not need arbitration as a protection against lawsuits. Tesla has said &#8221;We do the work required to ensure that our culture is as diverse and inclusive as it is collaborative and driven.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">7</sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">After the Board of a company with 74,000 employees conducted the study requested by this proposal it changed its use of arbitration in cases alleging discrimination and altered the charter of its compensation committee to include workplace culture.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt;padding-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:73.33%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:3pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup></font><font style="font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;">https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1318605/000156459020027321/tsla-def14a_20200707.htm</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">https://casetext.com/case/balan-v-tesla-motors-inc-1</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">https://www.hnlr.org/2020/08/forced-into-employment-arbitration-sexual-harassment-victims-are-saying- metoo-and-beginning-to-fight-back-but-they-need-congressional-help/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">22</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">https://www.eeoc.gov/eeoc/systemic/review/</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">6</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">https://www.law.com/therecorder/2020/09/25/google-ends-mandatory-arbitration-in-310m-sexual-harassment-settlement/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">7</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">https://www.tesla.com/sites/default/files/downloads/2020-DEI-impact-report.pdf</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_Hlk35955841"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD6"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD6"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;">The Board has considered this proposal and determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders. As with the similar proposal presented by this lead proponent at the 2020 annual meeting of stockholders, which was rejected by Tesla&#8217;s stockholders, the proponent cites inaccurate and unsupported assertions regarding arbitration and its alleged impact on workplace conditions at Tesla. </font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As noted in our response to the proponent&#8217;s proposal in 2020, Tesla&#8217;s standard arbitration provision specifically states that the parties are entitled to all remedies available in a court of law. The fact that a claim is not adjudicated by a court or does not have certain procedural aspects does not mean that legal remedies are not available through arbitration. Arbitration offers an alternative form of adjudication by an experienced jurist selected with both parties&#8217; participation that is often quicker than trial, especially in jurisdictions where courts are overburdened. Outcomes are also more certain because they may not be appealed absent extraordinary circumstances. Moreover, the employer bears the burden of paying the entire cost of the proceedings. The overall expediency benefits both parties with a fair resolution and a speedier return to their respective priorities without miring them in lengthy litigation. Notwithstanding the proponent&#8217;s generalizations that &#8220;companies with effective human capital management programs&#8221; do not mandate arbitration, we believe that the use of arbitration provisions remain very prevalent among many companies for all the reasons described herein, among others. Furthermore, outside of the U.S., where Tesla&#8217;s offer letters do not include arbitration provisions, many countries use specialized labor court proceedings similar to arbitration to adjudicate employee claims.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The proponent also fails to explain how arbitration prevents Tesla employees from learning about shared concerns or reduces willingness to report claims. An employee is free to publicize the results of an arbitration (as long as it excludes any trade secrets or proprietary business information), and to initiate a lawsuit by first filing a complaint in court. Similarly, while the proponent notes certain Tesla employees have alleged claims against the company, the proponent does not state any support for a correlation between employee arbitration and the alleged claims. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU28"></a>The<font style="Background-color:#FFFFFF;"> proponent&#8217;s one-size-fits-all goal appears to be that every company simply eliminate employee arbitration; but the proponent fails to clearly or adequately explain the benefits to Tesla or our stockholders for doing so. </font>The proponent claims that various governmental bodies may be considering or taking steps to curtail the use of arbitration but does not specify how any such developments would adversely impact Tesla or our stockholders (or argue that Tesla would not comply with applicable legal or regulatory requirements). Similarly, the proponent makes conclusory statements about other, and generally unnamed and unquantified, companies and th<a name="_AEIOULastRenderedPageBreakAEIOU28"></a>eir arbitration policies without considering or specifying how such other companies may or may not be similarly situated to Tesla. By contrast, the Board believes that each company is unique and should not be governed by sweeping and unsubstantiated generalizations. In the case of Tesla, our mission is to accelerate the world&#8217;s transition to sustainable energy. Implicit in our mission is a mandate to not only follow the law, but to do the right thing. As we have pledged in our annual Impact Report, Tesla has designed our workplace and policies to provide all employees with a respectful and safe working environment by not tolerating any discrimination, harassment, retaliation or any other mistreatment at work, whether based on a legally protected status or otherwise. Therefore, we reiterate that Tesla, its employees and its stockholders would be better served by continuing to execute on our mission and tangible workplace goals rather than devote attention and resources to reporting on an issue as to which the proponent has inaccurately characterized the fundamental premise and which is a pretext for its narrowly-focused goal.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding reporting on employee arbitration.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">23</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_EIGHT8"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_EIGHT8"></a>PROPOSAL EIGHT</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ASSIGNING RESPONSIBILITY FOR STRATEGIC OVERSIGHT OF HUMAN CAPITAL MANAGEMENT TO AN INDEPENDENT BOARD-LEVEL COMMITTEE</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with SEC rules, we have set forth below a stockholder proposal, along with a supporting statement, exactly as submitted by the Comptroller of the City of New York, which is the custodian and a trustee of the New York City Teachers&#8217; Retirement System, New York City Employees&#8217; Retirement System and the Board of Education Retirement System (the &#8220;<font style="text-decoration:underline;">Systems</font>&#8221;). The Comptroller of the City of New York has notified us the Systems are beneficial owners of 151,745 shares of Tesla&#8217;s common stock and intends to present the following proposal at the 2021 Annual Meeting through its designee, the Comptroller of the City of New York. The Comptroller of the City of New York&#8217;s address is One Centre Street, 8<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">th</sup> Floor North, New York, NY 10007-2341. The stockholder proposal will be required to be voted upon at the 2021 Annual Meeting only if properly presented.&#160;&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME8"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME8"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">RESOLVED: <font style="font-weight:normal;">That the Tesla, Inc. (&#8220;Tesla&#8221;) Board of Directors assign responsibility for strategic oversight</font><font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">of human capital management to an independent board-level committee. The committee&#8217;s responsibilities </font><font style="letter-spacing:-2.65pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">should</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;"> </font><font style="font-weight:normal;">include:</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">1.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Reviewing, on an ongoing basis, corporate policies and practices on principles, strategy and</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">management of workforce-related matters, including those related to addressing workforce equity </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-2.65pt;color:#000000;">&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">and inclusion,</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">and</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">compensation for</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">employees</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">other</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">than</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">executive</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">officers;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:9.07%;text-indent:-4.54%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">2.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Oversight</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">of</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">the</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">extent</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">to</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">which</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Tesla&#8217;s</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">policies,</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">standards</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">and</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">requirements</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">are</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">applied</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:0.05pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">consistently</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">across its operations,</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">and;</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-left:9.07%;text-indent:-4.54%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p></td>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"><font style="font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-decoration:none;Background-color:#auto;color:#auto;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">3.</font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="text-align:left;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;color:#auto;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;font-family:Calibri;font-size:11pt;"><font style="Background-color:#auto;text-decoration:none;"></font><font style="color:#000000;"></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">Offering</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.2pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">guidance</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">on</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">strategic</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">decisions</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">that</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">may</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.3pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">have</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">an</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">impact</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">on</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.15pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">the</font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;color:#000000;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;color:#000000;">workforce.</font></p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Supporting<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>Statement:</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:bold;;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Citing<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>multiple<font style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt;"> </font>claims<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt;"> </font>labor<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>rights<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>violations,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt;"> </font>including<font style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt;"> </font>discriminatory<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt;"> </font>anti-union<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>activities,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt;"> </font>MSCI<font style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt;"> </font>ESG<font style="letter-spacing:-2.65pt;"> </font>Ratings warned investor clients in September 2020 that &#8220;Tesla&#8217;s weak labor management practices may<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>pose<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>risks<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>company&#8217;s<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>growth<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>strategy.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup><font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>To date,<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>has<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>not<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>established<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>clear<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>oversight<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>responsibilities for its workforce at the board level or provided sufficient information for investors to<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>understand its human<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>capital<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>management<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>approach.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">High-profile killings of Black men and women in 2020 highlighted the grave consequences of systemic racism in our society, sparked nationwide protests for racial justice. They prompted many companies to publicize their commitments to racial equity and diversity. CEO Elon Musk&#8217;s only apparent action in support of Black employees during this period was to announce <font style="font-style:italic;">on the morning</font> of Juneteenth that it was an <font style="font-style:italic;">unpaid</font> holiday.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup> Many employees were already at work by the time the email was sent out.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In May 2020, the company reopened its plant, breaching government stay-at-home mandates. In the<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>months that followed, 450 employees tested positive for the coronavirus. The CEO reportedly dared state<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">officials</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">to</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">arrest</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">him.</font><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup><font style="letter-spacing:0.5pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">Despite</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">assurances</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>that<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>workers<font style="letter-spacing:-0.6pt;"> </font>could<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>stay<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>home<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>if<font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;"> </font>they<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>felt<font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;"> </font>unsafe,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>several<font style="letter-spacing:-0.4pt;"> </font>workers<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>were<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>subsequently<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>terminated<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>for &#8220;failure<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>return<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>work.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4</sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The CEO&#8217;s responses to both the pandemic and racial-justice protests underscore the need for broader<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>board oversight<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:0.1pt;"> </font>the<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>workforce.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s stated mission is &#8220;to accelerate the world&#8217;s transition to sustainable energy.&#8221;<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>This shift towards a<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>low-carbon economy is underway, with companies poised to significantly expand their operations and<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>workforce. It is essential that the low-carbon economy not replicate &#8211; or worse, exacerbate &#8211; the old<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>economy&#8217;s inequalities. Empirical studies show that robust human capital management is associated with:<font style="letter-spacing:-2.65pt;"> </font>improved recruitment and retention, better returns and lower costs, better brand reputation, improved<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>operational<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>performance,<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>better<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>long-term<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>strategic<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>planning<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup>.<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>The<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>need<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>for<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>board<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>oversight<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">responsibility</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.7pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">of</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">human</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">capital</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">management</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">reflects</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;">its</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>importance<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>company&#8217;s<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>strategy<font style="letter-spacing:-0.65pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>operations.<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>It<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>is<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>necessary<font style="letter-spacing:-0.5pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>enable<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>optimize<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>performance<font style="letter-spacing:-0.55pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>uphold<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>its<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>obligations<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>its<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>growing<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>workforce.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">To facilitate a just transition toward an environmentally sustainable economy, Tesla will need its board of<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>directors<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>oversee<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>a<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>credible<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>robust<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>long-term<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>strategy.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>Conversely,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font>failure<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>correctly<font style="letter-spacing:-0.45pt;"> </font>assign<font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font>board-<font style="letter-spacing:-2.7pt;"> </font>level oversight may create reputational and legal risks that can negatively impact performance and long-term<font style="letter-spacing:0.15pt;"> </font>value.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">24</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">These</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">are</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">significant</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">risks</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">for</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">shareholders.</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.35pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">We</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.3pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">urge</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">shareholders</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">to</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">vote</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font><font style="font-weight:bold;">FOR</font><font style="font-weight:bold;letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">this</font><font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">proposal.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt;padding-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:73.33%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">

<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.2pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"></font>n.d.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>MSCI<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>ESG<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>Ratings<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>Report.</p></td></tr></table></div>

<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
