<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">Lambert, F. and Lambert, F., 2021. Tesla makes Juneteenth a holiday as Elon Musk gets pressure from Black Lives<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>Matter movement - Electrek. [online] Electrek. Available at:<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>https://electrek.co/2020/06/19/tesla-juneteenth-holiday-elon-musk-pressure-black-lives-matter/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.25pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"></font>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Washington<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Post.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>2021.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Hundreds<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>of<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>covid<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>cases<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>reported<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>at<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>plant<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>following<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>Musk&#8217;s<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>defiant<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>reopening,<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>county data shows. [online] Available at: https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2021/03/12/hundreds-covid-cases-reported-tesla-plant-following-musks-defiant-reopening-county-data-shows/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">4 </sup></font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"></sup>The<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>Washington<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>Post.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>2020.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>Tesla<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>gave<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>workers<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>permission<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>to<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>stay<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>home<font style="letter-spacing:-0.25pt;"> </font>rather<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>than<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>risk<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>getting<font style="letter-spacing:-0.2pt;"> </font>covid-19.<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>Then<font style="letter-spacing:-0.15pt;"> </font>it<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>sent termination notices. [online] Available at: https://www.washingtonpost.com/technology/2020/06/25/tesla-plant-firings/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">5</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">The Harvard Law School Forum on Corporate Governance. 2021. Corporate Director Selection and Recruitment: A<font style="letter-spacing:-2.15pt;"> </font>Matrix. [online] Available at: https://corpgov.law.harvard.edu/2013/06/02/corporate-director-selection-and-recruitment-a-matrix/</p></td></tr></table></div>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD8"></a><a name="OPPOSING_STATEMENT__BOARD8"></a>Opposing Statement of the Board</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:6pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board has considered this proposal and has determined that it would not serve the best interests of Tesla or our stockholders, as Tesla already has in place a suitable governance structure for the oversight of human capital management. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The Board already has independent committees in place with oversight over the issues identified by the proponent. For example, the Compensation Committee of the Board plays a key role in overseeing human capital management at Tesla. Moreover, the individual members of the Compensation Committee of the Board have a diversity of expertise in human capital management from their professional experience with companies in a range of industries, including those with large and complex workforces. In addition to being tasked with monitoring and liaising with management regarding executive compensation at its standing meetings, the Compensation Committee reviews, considers and provides to management guidance related to workforce management, equity and inclusion,<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>and<font style="letter-spacing:-0.1pt;"> </font>compensation, recruiting and retention efforts for<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>employees<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>other<font style="letter-spacing:0.05pt;"> </font>than<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>executive<font style="letter-spacing:-0.05pt;"> </font>officers. As part of its broad oversight of Tesla&#8217;s material risks and compliance burdens, the Audit Committee of the Board also regularly receives updates from and provides feedback to management relating to various workforce issues including environmental, health and safety incident metrics and enterprise risk assessments pertaining to human resources. As such, the responsibilities requested by the proponent for an independent board-level committee are already generally being performed by independent committees of the Board. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In addition, the proponent cites as primary support for the proposal a number of media headlines relating to aspects of Tesla&#8217;s business operations. Aside from referencing one-sided allegations lacking full context and facts or drawing speculative conclusions from them, the proponent fails to support how such aspects of Tesla&#8217;s business operations are attributable to the existence or non-existence of an independent Board committee with oversight over issues of human capital management. Instead, such support points to incendiary storylines rather than actual correlation.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Although Board committees generally do not have granular responsibility for the day-to-day operations at companies they oversee, the Compensation Committee and Audit Committee of Tesla&#8217;s Board already provide important strategic reviews and guidance in this area. More broadly, Tesla&#8217;s DEI efforts, including those described in our annual Impact Report, illustrate our focus on attracting, developing and retaining top talent while integrating DEI principles and practices into our core values. Independent members of our Board regularly engage with our human resources leadership to review and align with Tesla&#8217;s DEI progress and provide feedback as to the effectiveness of its program. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Therefore, we believe we are already well-equipped to address human capital management issues, including with the support of an independent committee of the Board.</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-variant: small-caps;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;">The Board recommends a vote <font style="font-style:italic;">AGAINST</font> the stockholder proposal regarding assigning responsibility for strategic oversight of human capital management to an independent board-level committee.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-top:12pt;margin-bottom:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">25</a></p>
<hr style="page-break-after:always;width:100%;">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:10pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:11pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:0pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE"></a><a name="PROPOSAL_NINE"></a>PROPOSAL NINE</p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">STOCKHOLDER PROPOSAL REGARDING ADDITIONAL REPORTING ON HUMAN RIGHTS</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">In accordance with SEC rules, we have set forth below a stockholder proposal, along with a supporting statement, exactly as submitted by Sisters of the Good Shepherd New York Province. Sisters of the Good Shepherd New York Province has notified us that it is the beneficial owner of 35 shares of Tesla&#8217;s common stock and intends to present the following proposal at the 2021 Annual Meeting through its designee, Gina Falada. Sisters of the Good Shepherd New York Province&#8217;s address is 25-30 21st&#160;Avenue, Astoria, New York 11105. The stockholder proposal will be required to be voted upon at the 2021 Annual Meeting only if properly presented.&#160;</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:18pt;text-indent:0%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME7"></a><a name="STOCKHOLDER_PROPOSAL_SUPPORTING_STATEME7"></a>Stockholder Proposal and Supporting Statement </p>
<p style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:12pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:0%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">***</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Resolved: <font style="font-weight:normal;">Shareholders request that the Board of Directors commission an independent, third-party report assessing the extent to which Tesla is effectively fulfilling its responsibility to respect human rights and engage in responsible sourcing practices. The report should include analysis of how Tesla&#8217;s Code of Business Conduct and Ethics, Supplier Code of Conduct, and Human Rights and Conflict Minerals Policy are implemented to address adverse human rights impacts occurring within its direct operations and across the value chain. The report should exclude information relevant to any pending legal proceeding or threatened proceeding of which Tesla has notice.</font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-weight:bold;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Whereas: <font style="font-weight:normal;">Tesla sources thousands of parts from hundreds of global suppliers through complex, extended supply chains and acknowledges that &#8220;reliably determining the origin [of raw materials] is a difficult task.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">1</sup> Cobalt, conflict minerals, steel, lithium, rubber, mica, nickel, and electronics used in Tesla&#8217;s products may present human rights risks.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">2</sup></font></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Cobalt used in Tesla&#8217;s lithium-ion batteries can be traced to Glencore-owned mines in the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) where child labor is pervasive. Cobalt mining is one of the worst forms of child labor, requiring working with sharp tools in mines at risk of collapse. Tesla is a defendant in a class action lawsuit alleging it is &#8220;knowingly benefiting from and aiding and abetting the cruel and brutal use of young children in the [&#8220;DRC&#8221;] to mine cobalt.&#8221;<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup> In spite of its long&#173; term partnership with Glencore to annually source up to 6,000 tons of cobalt, Tesla&#8217;s motion to dismiss the lawsuit argued that it cannot control the actions of the mining companies in its supply chain. This conflicts with Tesla&#8217;s own &#8220;policies&#8221; that it will ensure these conditions do not occur in its supply chain and it will not tolerate the use of slave or child labor.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">As Tesla seeks to source more nickel for electric vehicle production, its failure to demonstrate responsible sourcing presents risks. Russian Indigenous activists urge Tesla not to source from Norilsk Nickel until it remediates devastating environmental, cultural, and economic harms from a major oil spill that impacted the traditional territory and livelihoods of Indigenous Peoples.<sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top"> 4</sup></p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">The National Labor Relations Board (NLRB) recently upheld a 2019 federal ruling that Tesla violated labor laws by blocking union organizing, and the company was ordered to reinstate a fired worker and remove an anti-union tweet by Elon Musk. Tesla also faces ongoing lawsuits alleging racial harassment and discrimination.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Additionally, Tesla&#8217;s factory conditions may violate the right to a safe and healthy workplace. Tesla&#8217;s Fremont, CA plant has a history of repeat fines for severe Occupational Safety and Health Administration (OSHA) violations. Insufficient safety trainings, noncompliant safety markings, exposure to toxins, and undercounting or mislabeling injuries have been documented. Tesla employees who raised concerns about the company&#8217;s insufficient response to COVID-19 faced retaliation amidst rising infections.</p>
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:12pt;text-indent:4.54%;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;">Tesla&#8217;s poor human rights performance suggests its human rights commitments are neither effectively implemented, contributing to positive human rights outcomes, nor ensuring access to remedy. </p>
<p style="margin-bottom:3pt;border-bottom:Solid 0.75pt;padding-bottom:1pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-right:73.33%;text-indent:0%;font-family:Times New Roman;font-size:6pt;">&nbsp;</p>
<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">

<td valign="top">

<td valign="top">

<div align="left">
<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"  style="border-collapse:collapse; width:100%;">
<tr>
<td valign="top" style="width:4.54%;white-space:nowrap">
<p style="margin-bottom:0pt;margin-top:3pt;font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"><sup style="font-size:85%;line-height:120%;vertical-align:top">3</sup></font><font style="font-size:10pt;font-family:Times New Roman;letter-spacing:-0.1pt;font-weight:normal;font-style:normal;text-transform:none;font-variant: normal;"> </font></p></td>
<td valign="top">
